The paper focuses on querying bibliographic metadata in the area of computer science, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it directly relates to the topic of the paper. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) are also likely categories as they deal with data retrieval and querying. cs.CL (Computational Linguistics) could be a possible category as the paper discusses the use of a domain-specific vocabulary. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper proposes a query language for accessing data.
